description:
As a Senior Product Manager - User Onboarding reporting to our Director of Product, you will be responsible for evolving and improving one of our key areas in TransferGo - Customer Journeys. This entails the translation of product value into quantitative terms. Together with Compliance, Marketing, other Product & Engineering teams you will be creating the strategy and executing product development to enable stakeholders with customisable features and providing our customers with best onboarding experience in the market. Our product is about providing seamless registration and onboarding experience while staying compliant.

Here’s what you’ll be doing:

Building product roadmaps, strategy and vision

You’ll be responsible for building a product roadmap while making use of data from secondary/primary research and requirement gathering, product analytics, competitor comparison, and other relevant business information. Additionally, we expect you to identify risks, challenges... opportunities and business integration needs and translate those into actionable deliverables. You will be owning a discovery track with multiple discovery items in parallel that touches and overlaps with other product areas.

Partnering with different level stakeholders

You’ll be working closely with C level executives, directors, engineering managers, other product managers and vendor’s delivery teams who will help to drive achieving key targets. You will spend your day-to-day working with software engineers who’ll help facilitate product development, drive and ensure alignment across multiple teams. You will partner a lot with Compliance, Marketing and other stakeholders to create amazing user experience.

Leading with ambition

You’ll be leading the team towards the success of the project while setting up target KPIs and pursuing OKRs. Together with your engineering manager you will be in charge of product deliveries and solutions that highly skilled developers will help you to achieve.

Ensuring clear communication & transparency

You’ll need to communicate effectively (speaking and writing in English) to ensure that plans, progress, and delivery are clearly understood across the organisation. We expect you to be self-organised and provide timely updates as well as feedback for your team members, peers and manager. Additionally, this team loves having a PM who is empathic and could enhance team’s motivation, thus, we expect you to be a true team player, who would be guiding the team towards understanding strategy, explaining what’s next and let them contribute to the roadmap building.

Here’s what we’d love from our new Senior Product Manager:
• You have some experience in fintech, preferably in consumer products related to customer onboarding/customer profile field;
• You have experience working with app/mobile applications and taking them to the next level;
• Your experience in Compliance, AML or Financial Crime fields, good understanding of processes and regulations related to different market areas would be considered as a huge plus;
• You have 3+ year product management experience building digital products at scale, with a track record of end-to-end product delivery in an agile environment;
• You focus on outcomes, not outputs;
• You are a true problem solver with a strong analytical mindset and a data-informed approach, you know how to do crisis management and help team to overcome challenges;
• You have excellent communication and stakeholder management skills, working effectively across a variety of functions and levels, incl. external parties;
• You are comfortable reacting fast, adapting to changing environment, challenging the team and prioritising sharply;
• You are fluent in English
